import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median Delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data["distance"], color="skyblue")
    ax.axvline(data["distance"].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Distance: {:.2f}'.format(data["distance"].mean()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    ax = sns.barplot(x='count', y='origin', hue='destination', data=data, dodge=False)
    ax.set(xlabel='Number of Flights', ylabel='Origin Airport')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['delay', 'distance']]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='distance', y='delay', data=data, alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Date', ylabel='Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
